cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with controlled natural language (CNL) editors for knowledge engineering. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as building a knowledge base is a common task in AI. The use of eye-tracking and screen recordings suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves identifying competencies and problems, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
